from sklearn.metrics import classification_report
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix


def evaluate_model(model, X_train, Y_train, X_test, Y_test):
    Y_train_pred = model.predict(X_train)
    Y_test_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    train_accuracy = accuracy_score(Y_train_pred, Y_train)
    test_accuracy = accuracy_score(Y_test_pred, Y_test)
    report = classification_report(Y_test, Y_test_pred)
    conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(Y_test, Y_test_pred)
    
    print(f"Model: {model.__class__.__name__}")
    print("Training Accuracy:", train_accuracy)
    print("Test Accuracy:", test_accuracy)
    print("Classification Report:\n", report)
    print("Confusion Matrix:\n", conf_matrix)
    print("\n")

from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, roc_auc_score

# Your existing model training
clf = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='entropy', ccp_alpha=0.1) 
clf = clf.fit(X_train, Y_train)
y_pred = clf.predict(X_test)

# Predicted probabilities for each class
y_pred_proba = clf.predict_proba(X_test)

# Calculate metrics
acc = accuracy_score(Y_test, y_pred)
pre = precision_score(Y_test, y_pred, average='macro')
rec = recall_score(Y_test, y_pred, average='macro')

# AUC calculation for binary classification
auc = roc_auc_score(Y_test, y_pred_proba[:, 1])  # Use probabilities for the positive class

print('accuracy =', acc, ', precision =', pre, ', recall =', rec, ', AUC =', auc)

from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score

# Define a range of k values to test
k_values = range(1, 50, 5)  # Testing odd values from 1 to 49

best_k = 0
best_accuracy = 0

# Loop over k values
for k in k_values:
    # Initialize the KNN model
    knn_model = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=k)

    # Fit the model
    knn_model.fit(X_train, Y_train)

    # Predict on the test set
    y_pred = knn_model.predict(X_test)

    # Calculate accuracy
    acc = accuracy_score(Y_test, y_pred)

    # Print the results
    print(f'K = {k}, Accuracy: {acc}')

    # Check if this is the best accuracy
    if acc > best_accuracy:
        best_accuracy = acc
        best_k = k

# Print the best k value
print(f'The best k value is: {best_k} with an accuracy of {best_accuracy}')
